public class SBNotice
extends java.lang.Object

This class is used to create scheduled behaviour notices stored on the sbl (scheduled behaviour list).

Gilbert Arbez

Method Detail

compareTo

public int compareTo(SBNotice sbn)
Compares SBNotice instances according to terminationTime and seqNum. The attribute seqNum is a private, and used to store SBNotice instances using FIFO on the sbl when the terminationTimes are for different instances.

Specified by:
compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<SBNotice>
Parameters:
sbn - - Reference to SBNotice instance to compare to this instance.
Returns:
-1, this SBNotice comes before sbn SBNotice. 1, this SBNotice comes after sbn SBNotice 0, they are the same notice

equals

public boolean equals(java.lang.Object sbn)
Determines if both this instance and sbn objects are equal, that is both terminationTime and the private seqNum attribute are the same.
